Social Media Checklist for College Students

 Do’s
- Think before posting any content online.
- Use strong privacy settings to protect personal information.
- Be respectful and polite in all online interactions.
- Verify information before sharing it.
- Maintain a positive and professional online presence.

 Don’ts
- Do not share personal or sensitive information publicly.
- Avoid engaging in online arguments or cyberbullying.
- Do not post inappropriate or offensive content.
- Avoid spreading rumors or fake news.
- Do not use weak passwords or share your login details.
